$ Oracle Autonomous Database

{ Promises

  Oracle Autonomous Database promises
    • to deliver automated → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/patching[patching] and upgrades
    • automated tuning
    • to minimize human error and human labor
    • eliminate routine maintenance tasks (provisioning, scaling, → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/patching[patching], tuning, …)
    • → development/Artificial-intelligence prevents, detects and responds to performance issues and cybersecurity issues.
    • security


  → development/databases/DBA[DBAs] won't go out of job, however. Rather, they will use their skill for even more important tasks at an organization.

}
{ Claims

  Oracle claims to be the world's first vendor to deliver an autonomous → development/databases[database].

}
{ Some features

 ~Replay production workload~ on a test database to make sure that an upgrade does not have unexpected side effects on the production DB.

 ~Load and go~ architecture: database tunes itself and creates or drops indexes.

 ~Security patches~ are automatically applied every quarter. Patches for *zero day exploits* are applied off-cycle.

 ~Oracle Autonomous Transaction Processing~ allows to run mission-critical enterprise applications, including mixed workloads and real-time analytics.

}
{ Technology

  These goals are achieved with
    • → development/Data/science/Machine-learning[Machine learning]

}
